  "source_file": "4ee4d6.ot2.apiv2.py",
  "intent_precise": "4ee4d6.ot2.apiv2: Using temp_block (labware, slot 2), tc_plate (pcr_plate, slot 4), mag_plate (pcr_plate, slot 6), sample_plate (pcr_plate, slot 1). With Temperature Module module, thermocycler module, magnetic module. (1) Open thermocycler lid. (2) Disengage magnets to release beads. (3) Transfer 138\u00b5L from wells eblt, tbs to empty 1, empty 1 within reagents_block. (4) Transfer 30\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (5) Operate thermocycler. (6) Close thermocycler lid. (7) Run thermocycler profile for 1 cycles. (8) Open thermocycler lid. (9) Transfer 10\u00b5L from reagents_block st2 to destination A1. (10) Mix 10 times at 50\u00b5L. (11) Transfer 60\u00b5L from source A1 to destination A1. (12) Incubate for 5 minutes. (13) Engage magnets for bead separation. (14) Pause for incubation. (15) Transfer 60\u00b5L from source A1 to reagents_res waste. (16) Disengage magnets to release beads. (17) Pause: Please refill the p300 tip box. (18) Transfer 100\u00b5L from reagents_res twb to destination A1. (19) Engage magnets for bead separation. (20) Transfer from reagents_block (epm, water) to destination (A1, A1). (21) Mix 10 times at 200\u00b5L. (22) Pause for incubation. (23) Transfer 100\u00b5L from source A1 to reagents_res waste. (24) Disengage magnets to release beads. (25) Transfer 45\u00b5L from reagents_block (empty 2, A1) to destination (A1, A1). (26) Pause: Please remove the 96 well plate from the thermocycler\n                 and add 10 ul from the index adapter plate to A3-H3, A4-B4.\n                 Then return the plate to the thermocycler. (27) Mix 10 times at 40\u00b5L. (28) Close thermocycler lid. (29) Operate thermocycler. (30) Run thermocycler profile for reps cycles. (31) Set temperature to 10\u00b0C. (32) Open thermocycler lid. (33) Pause: Part 1 - Tagmentation, Clean Up,\n                 Amplify Tagmented DNA steps are complete.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation, temperature control (10\u00b0C), thermocycling. (volumes 10\u00b5L-200\u00b5L, ~6 min total)",
  "intent": "For this tagmentation and amplification protocol, start by opening the thermocycler lid and disengaging the magnetic module to release any beads, then transfer 138\u00b5L from the eblt and tbs wells to the empty wells in the reagents block. Transfer 30\u00b5L from source plate A1 to the thermocycler plate A1, run one thermocycler cycle, then add 10\u00b5L of st2 reagent and mix 10 times at 50\u00b5L before transferring 60\u00b5L back to the magnetic plate for a 5-minute incubation with magnet engagement. After removing the supernatant to waste, perform a wash with 100\u00b5L of twb buffer, then add your epm and water reagents with 10x mixing at 200\u00b5L, followed by another wash step and final addition of 45\u00b5L from empty well 2. You'll need to manually add 10\u00b5L index adapters to wells A3-H3 and A4-B4 when prompted, then mix 10 times at 40\u00b5L and run the final thermocycler program ending at 10\u00b0C to complete the tagmentation and amplification steps.",
  "style": "scientist",
